An Artist Talk by Eric Baudelaire: Tisch School of the Arts at NYU                           Skip to content        Department of Cinema Studies _Copy Undergraduate Graduate MIAP Home Dual BA/MA Program Asian Film and Media Initiative (AFMI) Certificate in Culture and Media Financial Aid and Scholarships Course Offerings News & Events Faculty & Administration Alumni Cinema Resources Blog Announcements  home > Cinema Studies        An Artist Talk by Eric Baudelaire  Event Date and Time: October 1, 2014 6:15pm Location: Department of Cinema Studies, Michelson Theater 721 Broadway, 6th Floor New York, NY 10003 Unrealized Films, Unraveling Armies, Unrecognized States: An Artist Talk by Eric Baudelaire  The eclectic body of work by Paris-based artist and filmmaker Eric Baudelaire moves provocatively between playful and serious, documentary and fiction. Ranging from print, photography and the moving image to installation, performance and social practice, his work pries open political and cultural histories, to displace familiar narratives of power and resistance; to question the modes of production and consumption of images; and to probe the relationship between images and events, documents and narratives. His films have been shown widely including at the New York Film Festival, Toronto International Film Festival, Locarno Film Festival, International Film Festival Rotterdam and FIDMarseille. His work has been exhibited in solo and group exhibitions at numerous venues including the Hammer Museum (Los Angeles), Gasworks (London), Bergen Kunsthall, and the Yokohama Triennial, and is included in the collections of the Whitney Museum of American Art, the Centre Pompidou, and the MACBA (Barcelona).  Introduction by Toby Lee (NYU Cinema Studies). This event is free and open to the public. Reception to follow.
